<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-59-0990 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the British Sector of the North Sea there are 148 permanent structureoil and gas platforms. Many of the platforms are reaching the end oftheir productive lives. The legal obligations of the platform operators,as to the demobilisation of the installations, are not precisely defined.This paper explains briefly, the regulations governing demobilisation,as they stand at present, and examines in depth, a case study which detailsthe procedures and costs related to the various options available, usingpresent day equipment, for the decommissioning, removal and disposalof a typical North Sea installation.</TEXT></DOC>